codex
The first three findings are real in the current code: `createEvm` forwards the caller’s array, the mutators alter the array in place, and `Evm.create()` can leave `_customPrecompiles` undefined. I’m going to fix those by normalizing arrays at construction and replacing arrays in mutators instead of mutating shared references.
